# Docs

## Style

- Use tables for module/variable listings.
- Use mermaid diagrams for architecture flows.
- No emojis in docs.
- Keep tone factual and concise.

## Structure

Existing docs:

- `BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE.md` — API modules, auth, Prisma model outline
- `FRONTEND_ARCHITECTURE.md` — Web + admin stack and conventions
- `DEVOPS.md` — Env vars, Docker, HTTPS, BotFather
- `PRODUCT_ARCHITECTURE.md` — Personas, user journeys

## When adding docs

- Do not create new top-level docs without updating the table in `README.md`.
- Cross-link related docs instead of duplicating content.
